## JSX to Vue SFC Conversion

### 1. React Function Component → Vue SFC with `<script setup>`

**React:**

```jsx
function ProductCard({ product, onAddToCart }) {
    const [quantity, setQuantity] = useState(1);

    return (
        <div>
            <h3>{product.name}</h3>
            <input type="number" value={quantity} onChange={e => setQuantity(+e.target.value)} />
            <button onClick={() => onAddToCart(product.id, quantity)}>Add</button>
        </div>
    );
}
```

**Vue SFC (`<script setup>`):**

```vue
<!-- resources/js/Components/ProductCard.vue -->
<script setup>
import { ref } from 'vue';

// Props — replaces React function arguments
const props = defineProps({
    product: Object,
});

// Emits — replaces React callback props (onAddToCart)
const emit = defineEmits(['add-to-cart']);

// ref() replaces useState()
const quantity = ref(1);

const handleAdd = () => {
    emit('add-to-cart', props.product.id, quantity.value);
};
</script>

<template>
    <div>
        <h3>{{ product.name }}</h3>
        <!-- v-model replaces controlled input + onChange -->
        <input type="number" v-model.number="quantity" />
        <button @click="handleAdd">Add</button>
    </div>
</template>
```

